The calculated maximum efficiencies of the cation-doped and undoped MA(FA)PbI3. The violet, blue, black, red, green, and yellow lines represent the maximum efficiencies of the Sn-doped MAPbI3, TI-doped MAPbI3, un-doped MAPbI3, Sn-doped FAPbI3, TI-doped MAPbI3 and un-doped MAPbI3, respectively.

To know the difficulty of Bi, Sn, and TI doping in the MAPbI3 and FAPbI3, the formation energy, Ef, is calculated. The formation energy of the cation-doped MAPbI3/FAPbI3 is defined as follows,1Ef=Etotal-Epure+μPb-μcation\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
